      • putAllInternal

        protected void putAllInternal(Map<? extends Object,? extends Object> m)
        This Operation will first group all puts per partition and then send a PutAllOperation per partition. So if there are e.g. 5 keys for a single partition, then instead of having 5 remote invocations, there will be only 1 remote invocation.

        If there are multiple puts for different partitions on the same member, they are executed as different remote operations. Probably this can be optimized in the future by making use of an PartitionIterating operation.

        Parameters:
        m -
